Usage: set_multi_input_switching_mode [-help] [-disable_lib_cells <string>]
                                      [-mis_alignment_mode {0 1}]
                                      [-nsigma_multiplier <float>]
                                      [-switching_alignment_factor <float>]
                                      [-transition_factor_in_timing_window <float>]
                                      [-view <string>]

-help                                   # Prints out the command usage
-disable_lib_cells <string>             # To disable or enable MIS support for
                                        # given library cell. (string, optional)
-mis_alignment_mode {0 1}               # This mode eliminates the inputs that
                                        # are switching much earlier than the
                                        # main input, which may cause large
                                        # negative delays. (enum, optional)
-nsigma_multiplier <float>              # (float, optional)
-switching_alignment_factor <float>     # Used to configure relative alignment
                                        # of side inputs switching with
                                        # respective to primary input to tune
                                        # impact of MIS. It's value varies
                                        # between -1 to 1.
                                        # (float, optional, min=-1, max=1)
-transition_factor_in_timing_window <float>
                                        # (float, optional, min=0, max=1)
-view <string>                          # Specify view for the multi input
                                        # switching alignment mode.
                                        # (string, optional)